@bg 2.6: logical operations
@bh logical shifts
@bi AND
@bj OR
@bk NOT
@bl NOR
@bm A NOR D = NOT(A or D) = NOT(A)
@bn andi: and immediate
@bo ori: or immediate
@1p 2.7: instructions for making decisions
@1q conditional branches: an instruction that requires the comparison of two values
and that allows for a subsequent transfer of control
to a new address in program based on outcome of the comparison
@1r beq: branch if equal
@1s bne: branch if not equal
@1t unconditional branch
@1u loops
@1v basic block: seq of instr without branches (except
possibly at end), and without branch targets/labels
(except possibly at beginning)
@1w early phase compiliation: breaking program into smaller
blocks
@1x check if var less than another var
@1y slt: set on less than
@1z slti: immediate slt
@20 no branch on LT in MIPS
@21 too complicated: stretch clock cycle time of take extra
clock cycles per instruction
@22 signed vs unsigned in comparison instructions
@23 sltu/sltiu: set on LT unsigned
@24 treating signed numbers as unsigned: low cost way to
check of $0 \le x < y$
@25 matches index out of bounds check
for arrays
@26 case/switch statement
@27 chain of if-then-else-statements
@28 jump address table / jump table
table of addresses for alternative instruction
sequences
@29 jump register (jr)
